Do this each run:
1) List open PRs in BillChirico/bills-bot.
2) Filter to ONLY Bill's PRs and Pip Build's PRs. Skip everything else.
3) For eligible PRs, count unresolved review threads.
4) If no unresolved threads on eligible PRs: respond exactly `NO_REPLY`.
5) If unresolved threads exist:
   - Spawn ONE sub-agent PER PR (parallel), never batch PRs together.
   - Use agentId `build`, model `anthropic/claude-opus-4-6`, thinking `high`.
   - Include full unresolved thread details (thread id, file path, line, issue summary).
   - Instruct spawned agents to read and follow CODING.md, fix all review comments (including nitpicks unless nonsensical/breaking/redundant), run tests/coverage, resolve threads.
   - Instruct spawned agents NOT to post PR summary comments unless Bill explicitly asks.
   - Have spawned agents report completion summary back to parent agent.
   - After spawning, send Bill a concise Discord DM status update:
     - channel: discord
     - target: user:191633014441115648
     - accountId: pip-build
     - include PR numbers and unresolved thread counts.
6) If any spawned run fails/stalls, note it in DM and respawn once.

Keep updates concise and action-oriented.

content.thinking:
**Initiating PR Review Process**

I'm establishing the PR review patrol for the `bills-bot` repo. My objective is to create a high-frequency cron job. The core logic will involve listing open pull requests in `BillChirico/bills-bot`. I'm going to filter this list and prioritize PRs from `BillChirico` and `Pip`.


**Adapting PR Review Script**

I'm adapting the existing script from `HEARTBEAT.md` to list open PRs and their unresolved threads. It already filters for `BillChirico`, which is helpful. I'll also add a filter for "Pip Build" PRs. Then, I will need to determine the current user's identity to avoid unnecessary noise.

arguments.command:
cd /home/bill/.openclaw/workspace-build/bills-bot/

# Get open PRs authored by BillChirico (our primary identity)
# Note: gh pr list --author @me might also work but BillChirico is explicit.
PR_LIST=$(gh pr list --state open --author BillChirico --json number,title,headRefName --jq '.[] | @base64')

if [ -z "$PR_LIST" ]; then
  echo "No eligible PRs found."
  exit 0
fi

for pr_b64 in $PR_LIST; do
  pr=$(echo "$pr_b64" | base64 --decode)
  PR_NUM=$(echo "$pr" | jq -r '.number')
  PR_TITLE=$(echo "$pr" | jq -r '.title')
  PR_BRANCH=$(echo "$pr" | jq -r '.headRefName')

  # Paginate through ALL review threads
  CURSOR=""
  TOTAL_UNRESOLVED=0
  THREAD_DETAILS=""
  
  while true; do
    if [ -z "$CURSOR" ]; then
      RESULT=$(gh api graphql -f query="{repository(owner:\"BillChirico\",name:\"bills-bot\"){pullRequest(number:$PR_NUM){reviewThreads(first:100){pageInfo{hasNextPage endCursor} nodes{id isResolved comments(first:1){nodes{path line body}}}}}}}")
    else
      RESULT=$(gh api graphql -f query="{repository(owner:\"BillChirico\",name:\"bills-bot\"){pullRequest(number:$PR_NUM){reviewThreads(first:100,after:\"$CURSOR\"){pageInfo{hasNextPage endCursor} nodes{id isResolved comments(first:1){nodes{path line body}}}}}}}")
    fi

    # Count unresolved in this page
    PAGE_UNRESOLVED_JSON=$(echo "$RESULT" | jq -c '.data.repository.pullRequest.reviewThreads.nodes[] | select(.isResolved == false)')
    
    if [ ! -z "$PAGE_UNRESOLVED_JSON" ]; then
      while read -r node; do
        if [ ! -z "$node" ]; then
          TOTAL_UNRESOLVED=$((TOTAL_UNRESOLVED + 1))
          T_ID=$(echo "$node" | jq -r '.id')
          T_PATH=$(echo "$node" | jq -r '.comments.nodes[0].path // "unknown"')
          T_LINE=$(echo "$node" | jq -r '.comments.nodes[0].line // "unknown"')
          T_BODY=$(echo "$node" | jq -r '.comments.nodes[0].body // "no comment body"' | head -n 1)
          THREAD_DETAILS="${THREAD_DETAILS}\n- ID: $T_ID | File: $T_PATH:$T_LINE | Summary: $T_BODY"
        fi
      done <<< "$PAGE_UNRESOLVED_JSON"
    fi

    HAS_NEXT=$(echo "$RESULT" | jq -r '.data.repository.pullRequest.reviewThreads.pageInfo.hasNextPage')
    if [ "$HAS_NEXT" = "true" ]; then
      CURSOR=$(echo "$RESULT" | jq -r '.data.repository.pullRequest.reviewThreads.pageInfo.endCursor')
    else
      break
    fi
  done

  echo "DATA_PR_NUM: $PR_NUM"
  echo "DATA_PR_TITLE: $PR_TITLE"
  echo "DATA_PR_BRANCH: $PR_BRANCH"
  echo "DATA_UNRESOLVED_COUNT: $TOTAL_UNRESOLVED"
  echo -e "DATA_THREAD_DETAILS: $THREAD_DETAILS"
  echo "---"
done
